# Hoot Frontend Development Rules

## File Size Limit
- NO file can exceed 500 lines of code
- Files longer than 500 lines MUST be broken down and refactored
- Split large files by logical sections/components

## Code Organization
- Each page should have its own folder with its own CSS file
- Shared styles should be in separate CSS modules
- Components should be in their own files/folders

## Design Principles
- Matte black background (#000000) with subtle variations per section
- Gold accent color (#d4af37) used strategically
- Professional, modern, sleek design
- Fully responsive - must look good on all screen sizes
- Mobile-first approach where possible

## Typography
- Body text: Poppins
- Headings: Outfit
- Material Icons for all icons (no emojis)

## Responsive Design
- All sections must be fully responsive
- Mobile layouts should be compact and well-organized
- Touch targets should be appropriately sized
- Text should be readable without zooming
- Spacing should be optimized for small screens

## Component Structure
- Each major section should be a separate component if reusable
- CSS should be organized by section/component
- Use CSS modules or separate CSS files per component

## Git Workflow
- Commit frequently with descriptive messages
- Push to main branch for auto-deployment to Vercel
